  * Limited feature complexity
  * HonestyMeter currently text-only

* Goal:

  * Build a **multi-layer intelligent media analysis system**:

    * Fake news detection
    * Bias detection (fine-grained)
    * Explainable AI for media transparency



# Plan of Development:
* Layer 1 — Inputs (beyond paste text)
The original project only takes raw text. You can add URL scraping (auto-fetch the article using newspaper3k), a claim+evidence mode for stance detection, and eventually image+caption analysis for multimodal misinformation.
* Layer 2 — NLP Analysis (your core)
You already have the TF-IDF + Logistic Regression model and HonestyMeter for bias/manipulation. The additions here are: a BERT/RoBERTa model for much better semantic understanding, sentiment + emotion analysis (high outrage/fear is a strong deception signal), named entity recognition to extract and fact-check specific people/orgs/dates, and a clickbait detector that checks whether the headline matches the body.
* Layer 3 — Source Credibility (missing completely from nishitpatel01)
This is a major gap in the original. You can pull from MediaBiasFactCheck or AllSides to score the publishing domain, check domain age/HTTPS/WHOIS signals (fake sites are often newly registered), look up author history if available, and cross-check whether other credible sources are reporting the same claim.
* Layer 4 — Explainability (the problem statement specifically demands this)
This is what separates a useful system from a black box. LIME/SHAP shows which words drove the prediction. Attention heatmaps (for BERT-based models) show exactly which spans the model focused on. A span highlighter marks misleading content inline in the original text. You should also retrieve similar known-fake articles so the user can see precedent.
* Layer 5 — Output
Beyond true/fake, you want a confidence score (e.g. 78% likely fake), a plain-English LLM-generated explanation of why, an exportable full report (JSON or PDF), and a user feedback loop so incorrect predictions can feed back to improve the model over time.